ru.jango.j0widget

Class FilenameComparator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.jango.j0widget.FilenameComparator<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<T>

    public class FilenameComparator<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<T>
    Special comparator for sorting lists of URIs, URLs, File objects etc.. In cmp(Object, Object) would be called Object.toString() on both objects, then filename would be extracted and then they would be compared. Like this:

    final String s1 = PathUtil.getFilenameWithoutExt(obj1.toString()); final String s2 = PathUtil.getFilenameWithoutExt(obj2.toString());

    See Also:
    Collections.sort(java.util.List, java.util.Comparator)
